				<div class="col entry_right">
						<h3><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/bruce-kushnick/verizon-ny-paid-virtually_b_9667024.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" style="line-height: 18px !important;font-weight: bold;font-size: 16px;font-family: arial;color: #1A1A1A;">Verizon NY Paid Virtually No Taxes Since 2003; Averaged $2.5+ Billion in Losses a Year for Five Years*</a></h3>
						<div class="green_entry_bar"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
		                 		
			      <div class="image_wrapper relative" style="width: 300px;float:left;">
				<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/bruce-kushnick/verizon-ny-paid-virtually_b_9667024.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" >
					<img src="http://i.huffpost.com/gen/2940756/images/r-VERIZON-medium.jpg" alt="VERIZON" />
				</a>
				
			     </div> 
	     	      			<p>Yes, it is tax season yet again and you probably paid more taxes than Verizon NY. (NOTE: Verizon's other incumbent phone companies  are using the same 'questionable' financial book keeping, but their accounting is not public.)</p>
				 
		   <div class="author_bottom_desc">
			  <div class="blogger_img">
						<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/bruce-kushnick/"><span id="blogger-headshot" style="background-image: url(http://s.huffpost.com/contributors/bruce-kushnick/headshot.jpg);"></span></a>
				</div>
				<div class="blogger_credit">
				   <p class="byline_timestamp blogger_name"><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/bruce-kushnick/">Bruce Kushnick</a></p>
				   <p class="author_teaser">Executive Director, New Networks Institute</p>
				</div>
		
		   </div>
		
		</div>
		
		
		
    	
	
		

					
				<div class="entry " id="blog_9635880" data-beacon='{"p":{"plid":9635880,"mpid":,"lnid":"autopilot"}}'>
				<div class="col entry_left">
				</div>
				<div class="col entry_right">
						<h3><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/roger-hickey/april-13-million-student-march-for-debt-reduction-politicians-better-have-some-solutions_b_9635880.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" style="line-height: 18px !important;font-weight: bold;font-size: 16px;font-family: arial;color: #1A1A1A;">April 13: Million Student March for Debt Reduction. Politicians Better Have Some Solutions.</a></h3>
						<div class="green_entry_bar"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
		                 		
			      <div class="image_wrapper relative" style="width: 300px;float:left;">
				<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/roger-hickey/april-13-million-student-march-for-debt-reduction-politicians-better-have-some-solutions_b_9635880.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" >
					<img src="http://i.huffpost.com/gen/4205836/images/r-I-AM-A-STUDENT-DEBT-VOTER-medium.jpg" alt="I AM A STUDENT DEBT VOTER" />
				</a>
				
			     </div> 
	     	      			<p>A new wave of activism against student debt is on the move again this week. The students taking the lead represent the advance guard of an even more massive army which is mobilizing around the idea that higher education should be an investment we make as a society.</p>
				 
		   <div class="author_bottom_desc">
			  <div class="blogger_img">
						<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/roger-hickey/"><span id="blogger-headshot" style="background-image: url(http://s.huffpost.com/contributors/roger-hickey/headshot.jpg);"></span></a>
