				<div class="col entry_right">
						<h3><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/robin-elizabeth-herr-phd/voting-for-the-next-gener_b_9641978.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" style="line-height: 18px !important;font-weight: bold;font-size: 16px;font-family: arial;color: #1A1A1A;">Voting for the Next Generation</a></h3>
						<div class="green_entry_bar"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
		                 		
			      <div class="image_wrapper relative" style="width: 300px;float:left;">
				<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/robin-elizabeth-herr-phd/voting-for-the-next-gener_b_9641978.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" >
					<img src="http://i.huffpost.com/gen/4008218/images/r-SUPREME-COURT-medium.jpg" alt="SUPREME COURT" />
				</a>
				
			     </div> 
	     	      			<p>Clearly, the Supreme Court nomination process has become hopelessly political. Reform is in order. But until that happens, the choice is left to us, the voters. This time, our vote is not just for the next four years, it is for the next generation.</p>
				 
		   <div class="author_bottom_desc">
			  <div class="blogger_img">
						<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/robin-elizabeth-herr-phd/"><span id="blogger-headshot" style="background-image: url(http://s.huffpost.com/contributors/robin-elizabeth-herr-phd/headshot.jpg);"></span></a>
				</div>
