				</div>
				<div class="col entry_right">
						<h3><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/nathaniel-haas/democrats-who-welcome-tru_b_9650770.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" style="line-height: 18px !important;font-weight: bold;font-size: 16px;font-family: arial;color: #1A1A1A;">Democrats Who Welcome Trump Are Playing a Most Dangerous Game</a></h3>
						<div class="green_entry_bar"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
		                 		
			      <div class="image_wrapper relative" style="width: 300px;float:left;">
				<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/nathaniel-haas/democrats-who-welcome-tru_b_9650770.html?utm_hp_ref=bernie-sanders" >
					<img src="http://i.huffpost.com/gen/1179852/images/r-UNEMPLOYMENT-DATA-CANADA-UNRELIABLE-medium.jpg" alt="UNEMPLOYMENT DATA CANADA UNRELIABLE" />
				</a>
				
			     </div> 
	     	      			<p>Folks on the left are happy to publicly gnash teeth every time Trump reminds the country he might actually be the fourth horseman of the apocalypse, but privately rejoice about the prospect of Hillary Clinton or Bernie Sanders running against him in the general election.</p>
				 
		   <div class="author_bottom_desc">
			  <div class="blogger_img">
						<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/nathaniel-haas/"><span id="blogger-headshot" style="background-image: url(http://s.huffpost.com/contributors/nathaniel-haas/headshot.jpg);"></span></a>
				</div>
				<div class="blogger_credit">
				   <p class="byline_timestamp blogger_name"><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/nathaniel-haas/">Nathaniel Haas</a></p>
